    ],
    "tutor": [
      {
        "text": "Hallo Luis! Willkommen zurück. Du hast das Deutsch-Akkusativ-A2-Thema gemeistert. Jetzt geht es um JavaScript-Debugging. Möchtest du mir neue Hausaufgaben zeigen oder eine Frage stellen?",
        "timestamp": 1772318893.274355
      },
      {
        "text": "Got it, let's go back to the accusative. Um, welches Thema genau geht es?",
        "timestamp": 1772318910.628766
      },
      {
        "text": "Ah, okay. I've put a reminder on the board about the basicsbasics, showing how \"der\" and \"ein\" change. Does that help you get started?",
        "timestamp": 1772318938.028987
      },
      {
        "text": "Sure thing! The core rule is that the accusative case is used for the \"direct object\"—the thing the verb is acting on. For example, if you say \"Ich kaufe einen Ball\" (\"I buy a ball\"), \"Ball\" is the object and goes in the accusative. Does that make sense?",
        "timestamp": 1772318951.413553
      },
      {
        "text": "Möchtest du einen Beispielsatz mit \"den\" bilden?",
        "timestamp": 1772318973.3623528
      }
    ]
  },
